        <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">limitation</ENAMEX> could be a differential follow-up rate between
        male and female <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">patients</ENAMEX>, leading to the apparent trend
        towards better <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">one-year</TIMEX> outcomes in the female <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">patients</ENAMEX>.
        Nonetheless, we do not believe that there was a systematic
